s/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/plus-circle.f37c4a9.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Pro" role="img" title="Pro" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb1"></span>Smooth and controlled power</li></ul></div><div class="css-aqsj2r ektooqb6"><h6 class="css-ytm8f ektooqb5">Cons</h6><ul class="css-1r2eg5o ektooqb4"><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb2"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/x-circle.32fa08e.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Con" role="img" title="Con" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb0"></span>Heavy</li><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb2"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/x-circle.32fa08e.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Con" role="img" title="Con" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb0"></span>Not built for mountain biking</li></ul></div></div><div class="css-0 e1kz309q1"><table class="css-165pmwm ekv9bgd3"><tbody><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">POWER</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">750W</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">WEIGHT</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">77 lb.</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">TOP SPEED</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">28 mph</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><p data-node-id="65" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><br></p><p data-node-id="66" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Aventon has been on a roll, with new models and revisions to existing platforms. The brand''s update to its Aventure fat tire e-bike is no exception. At first glance, there are not many big visual differences between the original Aventure and this second-generation model. However, once outside, the small changes feel huge.<br></p><p data-node-id="67" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Compared to the original Aventure (<a href="https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576257&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aventon.com%2Fproducts%2Faventure-ebike&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fbikes-gear%2Fa22132137%2Fbest-electric-bikes%2F&amp;xs=1&amp;xcust=%5Butm_source%7C%5Butm_campaign%7C%5Butm_medium%7C%5Bgclid%7C%5Bmsclkid%7C%5Bfbclid%7C%5Brefdomain%7Cwww.bicycling.com%5Bcontent_id%7Cd3e2a1e6-a1f1-4b66-94af-a513e9ba1f4e%5Bcontent_product_id%7C141f49d8-dec2-48d7-a756-4d15d9b65dab%5Bproduct_retailer_id%7C6b2f9204-4a7d-4e58-b3cd-4a265c714ee7%5Blt%7C" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.aventon.com/products/aventure-ebike" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="on sale for $1,500" data-href="https://www.aventon.com/products/aventure-ebike" data-vars-ga-product-id="141f49d8-dec2-48d7-a756-4d15d9b65dab" data-affiliate="true" data-affiliate-url="https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576257&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aventon.com%2Fproducts%2Faventure-ebike" data-affiliate-network="{}" data-vars-ga-media-role="" data-vars-ga-media-type="" data-vars-ga-product-brand="Aventon" data-vars-ga-product-price="$1,999.00" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="6b2f9204-4a7d-4e58-b3cd-4a265c714ee7" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="Aventon" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="Sport Watches" data-vars-ga-gallery-id="" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" class="body-link product-links css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0" data-skimlinks-tracking="[utm_source|[utm_campaign|[utm_medium|[gclid|[msclkid|[fbclid|[refdomain|www.bicycling.com[content_id|d3e2a1e6-a1f1-4b66-94af-a513e9ba1f4e[content_product_id|141f49d8-dec2-48d7-a756-4d15d9b65dab[product_retailer_id|6b2f9204-4a7d-4e58-b3cd-4a265c714ee7[lt|">on sale for $1,500</a>), the Aventure.2 rides much smoother. The new torque sensor allows more control over the acceleration of Aventure''s 750W rear hub motor, making the bike''s ride more intuitive. Some of our test riders found the previous model to have too much torque, particularly for lighter-weight riders or those new to e-bikes; the Aventure.2 remedied this fault.</p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-9-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-9" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_9" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_10__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><p data-node-id="68" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">In addition to the new torque sensor, the Aventure.2 has an updated head unit interface, integrated turn signals, front light, rear rack, and fenders. We found the Aventure.2 well-suited for commutes (especially on snowy days and gravel pathways) and off-road on doubletrack trails. The bike''s weight and components limit its functionality on singletrack for more aggressive mountain bike riding. <br></p><p data-node-id="69" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><em><a href="https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576257&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aventon.com%2Fproducts%2Faventure2-step-through-ebike&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fbikes-gear%2Fa22132137%2Fbest-electric-bikes%2F&amp;xs=1&amp;xcust=%5Butm_source%7C%5Butm_campaign%7C%5Butm_medium%7C%5Bgclid%7C%5Bmsclkid%7C%5Bfbclid%7C%5Brefdomain%7Cwww.bicycling.com%5Bcontent_id%7Cd3e2a1e6-a1f1-4b66-94af-a513e9ba1f4e%5Bcontent_product_id%7Ceecfac3d-ef1d-4b99-b043-280fa4a535c8%5Bproduct_retailer_id%7Cd92f5110-892c-49fb-8cc0-38c53ea2a171%5Blt%7C" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.aventon.com/products/aventure2-step-through-ebike" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="AVAILABLE IN STEP-THROUGH" rel="nofollow" data-vars-ga-ux-element="