" title="Pro" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb1"></span>Suspension fork and built in rack</li></ul></div><div class="css-aqsj2r ektooqb6"><h6 class="css-ytm8f ektooqb5">Cons</h6><ul class="css-1r2eg5o ektooqb4"><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb2"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/x-circle.32fa08e.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Con" role="img" title="Con" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb0"></span>Weight</li></ul></div></div><div class="css-0 e1kz309q1"><table class="css-165pmwm ekv9bgd3"><tbody><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">POWER</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">750W</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">WEIGHT</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">73.2 lb.</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">TOP SPEED</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">28 mph</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><p data-node-id="74" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Designed with a classic moto style, Ride1Up''s Cafe Cruiser has a casual ride feel. And it''s also practical with a built-in rack and light. The zippy 750W motor powers the Cruiser to 28mph (20mph using the throttle) while the suspension fork and 3-inch wide tires help smooth out the ride. Ride the Cafe Cruiser to the bar, along the boardwalk, or to Sunday morning brunch. Add an optional <a href="https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=74968X1576257&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fride1up.com%2Fproduct%2Felectric-bike-passenger-kit%2F&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fbikes-gear%2Fa22132137%2Fbest-electric-bikes%2F&amp;xs=1&amp;xcust=%5Butm_source%7C%5Butm_campaign%7C%5Butm_medium%7C%5Bgclid%7C%5Bmsclkid%7C%5Bfbclid%7C%5Brefdomain%7Cwww.bicycling.com%5Bcontent_id%7Cd3e2a1e6-a1f1-4b66-94af-a513e9ba1f4e%5Bcontent_product_id%7C7f0c88b9-ee1f-4f0d-bab0-0b429fc998ba%5Bproduct_retailer_id%7C818d2d35-6552-4b6e-a81f-4b40103