965-168e-41ee-9896-69c673dd625c[lt|psv">$4,000 at Specialized</a></div><a href="#product-834effae-c500-450a-a4b6-1e8e29e144e6" title="Read more about Turbo Vado 4.0 Step-Through" class="evurjsd0 css-a7zw0o epl65fo4">Read more</a></div></li></ul><button class="css-1v3w30i e1q7v6ei1">Show more</button></div><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><br></p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-0-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-0" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_0" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_1__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><hr data-node-id="10" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">The Three Classes of E-Bikes</h2><p data-node-id="12" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">After determining which style of bike is right for you, the next consideration is which class of e-bike best fits your needs. In the U.S., there are three classes, defined by the type of assist and how fast the motor will propel you. Most electric bikes are defined as class 1 or 3. Class 1 bikes have a motor (max 750w) that assists while pedaling up to 20 mph. Class 3, also known as “speed pedelec,” can have up to a 750w motor (aka 1-horsepower) but can assist you up to 28 mph. Both are allowed in most states and cities without needing a license. </p><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="13" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="gocycle folding bike ridden by aithne feay in brooklyn" title="gocycle folding bike ridden by aithne feay in brooklyn" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/gocycle-aithne-maegan-gindi-511-1668872868.jpg?resize=980:*" width="3000" height="2000" decoding="async" data-nimg="future" loading="lazy" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Maegan Gindi</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="14" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Class 2 models have become more popular with riders, especially at lower prices. These models have a throttle that can propel a bike up to 20 mph without needing continuous pedaling. </p><p data-node-id="15" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Some bikes blur the lines. <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a25334309/aventon-pace-500-review/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a25334309/aventon-pace-500-review/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Aventon’s popular Pace 500" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Aventon’s popular Pace 500</a>, for example, is technically a Class 3 e-bike in that it reaches speeds up to 28 mph, but it also has a throttle that tops out at 20 mph (the maximum legal speed for a throttle).</p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-1-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-1" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_1" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_2__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><div suppresshydrationwarning="" data-node-id="16" data-embed="editorial-link" class="embed css-0 e9hzx6g0"><aside class="css-xia9bi e6pr2lz5"><h6 class="css-1s0q3og e6pr2lz3"><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i0"></span><span class="css-8lle59 e6pr2lz1">Related Story</span><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i1"></span></h6><ul class="css-163cffn e6pr2lz4"><li class="css-6ivu69 e6pr2lz2"><a href="/bikes-gear/a25602653/cheap-electric-bikes/" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="The 8 Best Cheap E-Bikes You Can Buy Right Now" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Editorial Links" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a25602653/cheap-electric-bikes/" class="css-1bn7a5e epl65fo4"><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i0"></span><img src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/ride-ebikes-1640102503.jpg?crop=1xw:1xh;center,top&amp;resize=300:*" alt="best cheap electric bikes" title="best cheap electric bikes" width="120" height="540" decoding="async" loading="lazy" image-align="left" class="css-1l0uuk1 e6pr2lz0"><span class="css-8lle59 e6pr2lz1">The 8 Best Cheap E-Bikes You Can Buy Right Now</span><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i1"></span></a></li></ul></aside></div><hr data-node-id="17" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="18" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">Two E-Bike Terms to Know</h2><p data-node-id="19" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Torque:</strong>  Measured in newton meters (or Nm), torque is a rotational measurement of force—and the number to pay attention to when you want an idea of an e-bike motor’s output. More torque means more power off the line and more boost to your pedaling. The heavier the bike, the more torque it needs. Lighter road bikes typically have 30 to 40Nm of torque, and trail and cargo models (generally) have at least 80Nm. Most commuter bikes fall somewhere in between.</p><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="aventon level" title="Aventon Level" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0128-1628099424.jpg?resize=980:*" width="3000" height="2000" decoding="async" data-nimg="future" loading="lazy" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><div class="css-jt7yti e1xqj1sx1">Bicycling Deputy Editor Tara Seplavy makes adjustments while testing the Gold-Award-winning Aventon Level.  </div><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Trevor Raab</span></figcaption></div></div></div><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_2" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_3__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><p data-node-id="21" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong></strong><strong>Watt Hours</strong>: The size of an e-bike’s battery is measured in watt-hours (or Wh). This measurement represents the energy stored in the battery and how many watts it can deliver each hour. The higher the number, the longer the range, but the faster you go, the less range you get. So, if a 504Wh battery paired with a 500-watt motor gives you one hour of ride time at the highest assist, riding at about half that power will double your range.  </p><div suppresshydrationwarning="" data-node-id="22" data-embed="editorial-link" class="embed css-0 e9hzx6g0"><aside class="css-xia9bi e6pr2lz5"><h6 class="css-1s0q3og e6pr2lz3"><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i0"></span><span class="css-8lle59 e6pr2lz1">Related Story</span><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i1"></span></h6><ul class="css-163cffn e6pr2lz4"><li class="css-6ivu69 e6pr2lz2"><a href="/bikes-gear/a25836248/electric-bike-motor/" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="E-Bike Motors, Explained" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Editorial Links" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a25836248/electric-bike-motor/" class="css-1bn7a5e epl65fo4"><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i0"></span><img src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/e-bike-motor-index-1547246255.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=300:*" alt="Product, Auto part, Machine, Vehicle, " title="Product, Auto part, Machine, Vehicle, " width="120" height="540" decoding="async" loading="lazy" image-align="left" class="css-1l0uuk1 e6pr2lz0"><span class="css-8lle59 e6pr2lz1">E-Bike Motors, Explained</span><span aria-hidden="true" class="css-0 eh2fd3i1"></span></a></li></ul></aside></div><hr data-node-id="23" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="24" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">Other E-Bike Features to Consider</h2><p data-node-id="25" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Locking Battery</strong>: As electric bike options continue expanding, many brands now seamlessly integrate batteries to make the bike look sleeker (and more like a traditional non-assist bike). Most batteries lock to the bike and come with a key that lets you unlock and remove it, which serves multiple purposes: You can remove the battery and charge it off the bike, a locked battery deters (and hopefully prevents) a thief from stealing it, and an e-bike with the battery removed is safer for hauling on a bike rack and lighter for carrying up steps.<br></p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-3-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-3" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_3" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_4__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="26" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="aventon level" title="Aventon Level" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-level-0081-1628099419.jpg?resize=980:*" width="3000" height="2000" decoding="async" data-nimg="future" loading="lazy" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><div class="css-jt7yti e1xqj1sx1">A removable battery helps for charging off the bike.</div><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Trevor Raab</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="27" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Wider Tires: </strong>Because e-bikes can maintain higher speeds for longer periods than standard bikes, you want extra control. Wider tires provide better traction and the freedom to leave the pavement with little penalty, and a suspension fork will help tame some of the rougher roads you might explore. Good disc brakes are a must, too, for slowing a heavy bike at high speed. This is not a place to skimp.</p><p data-node-id="28" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Integrated Lights</strong>: Some e-bikes come with an integrated lighting system that turns on when you power up the bike. While this is an awesome feature to have, it’s not a deal-breaker if your bike isn’t equipped this way. With so many great <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20023360/8-bike-lights-we-love/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20023360/8-bike-lights-we-love/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="bike lights" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">bike lights</a> available, it’s just as easy to attach your own. <br></p><hr data-node-id="29" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="30" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="aventon abound" title="Aventon Abound" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-abound-0070-1677178593.jpg?crop=1.00xw:1.00xh;0,0&amp;resize=980:*" width="3000" height="2000" decoding="async" data-nimg="future" loading="lazy" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><div class="css-jt7yti e1xqj1sx1">During our e-bike evaluations, we checked the stability of kickstands and the cargo capacity of panniers.</div><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Trevor Raab</span></figcaption></div></div></div><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-4-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-4" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_4" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_5__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><h2 data-node-id="31" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">How We Tested</h2><p data-node-id="32" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Our team of experienced bike testers evaluated each model here on its overall quality, its safety features, handling, motor, battery life, and whether the components and features added to the overall quality of the ride. We tested most of these bikes on our local roads, commuting to and from work, using them to stock up on groceries and beer, and running their batteries down to officially see how long they last on one charge. </p><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="33" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="aventon pace 500" title="Aventon Pace 500" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/aventon-pace-500-2022-riding-0104-1648832368.jpg?resize=980:*" width="3000" height="2000" decoding="async" data-nimg="future" loading="lazy" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><div class="css-jt7yti e1xqj1sx1">Deputy Editor Tara Seplavy testing the Aventon Pace 500’s adjustable stem.</div><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Trevor Raab</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="34" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">A few bikes here were not available for testing. In those cases, we relied on the expertise of our test team, interviews with product managers, and rigorous 