ikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/electric-bikes/electric-road-bikes/domane-al-5/p/36145" data-vars-ga-product-brand="Trek" data-vars-ga-product-id="f9029d37-4e02-4774-a8a2-75153bd835a4" data-vars-ga-product-price="$3,500.00" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="5b11cf55-e8c8-482c-8781-5c26c3f05053" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="Europe" data-vars-ga-gallery-id="" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" data-vars-ga-sku="trekbikes_36145_5278156" data-vars-ga-magento-tracking="1" role="button" data-ab-label="ProdClick" class="product-btn-link en6kra60 css-17x8gcl epl65fo4" data-skimlinks-tracking="[utm_source|[utm_campaign|[utm_medium|[gclid|[msclkid|[fbclid|[refdomain|www.bicycling.com[content_id|d3e2a1e6-a1f1-4b66-94af-a513e9ba1f4e[content_product_id|f9029d37-4e02-4774-a8a2-75153bd835a4[product_retailer_id|5b11cf55-e8c8-482c-8781-5c26c3f05053[lt|">$3,500 at Trek Bikes</a></div></div></div><div class="css-tnkfjl ektooqb7"><div class="css-aqsj2r ektooqb6"><h6 class="css-ytm8f ektooqb5">Pros</h6><ul class="css-1r2eg5o ektooqb4"><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb3"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/plus-circle.f37c4a9.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Pro" role="img" title="Pro" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb1"></span>HyDrive hube motor</li><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb3"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/plus-circle.f37c4a9.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Pro" role="img" title="Pro" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb1"></span>Shimano 105 2x11 drivetrain</li><li class="css-9ee16j ektooqb3"><span aria-hidden="true" class=" css-4bs81v e1s64tyo0"><img data-dynamic-svg="" src="/_assets/design-tokens/fre/static/icons/plus-circle.f37c4a9.svg?primary=%2523067EA7" loading="lazy" alt="Pro" role="img" title="Pro" height="auto" width="auto" class="css-23kqqm ektooqb1"></span>3 colors and 6 sizes</li></ul></div><div class="css-aqsj2r ektooqb6"><h6 class="css-ytm8f ektooqb5">Cons</h6><ul class="css-1r2eg5o ektooqb4"></ul></div></div><div class="css-0 e1kz309q1"><table class="css-165pmwm ekv9bgd3"><tbody><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">Power</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">40Nm</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">Weight</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">31 lb.</td></tr><tr class="css-0 ekv9bgd2"><th class="css-1xje7yg ekv9bgd0">Top Speed</th><td class="css-13w75t5 ekv9bgd1">20 mph</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><p data-node-id="108" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">A great way to explore backroads or longer routes, electric-assist road bikes have opened up road cycling to more people. Trek''s 31-pound Domane+ road bike provides pedaling assistance up to 20 mph and approximately 55 miles (in Eco mode) via a 250W (40Nm) HyDrive hub motor and 250Wh internal battery. For longer rides, an optional range extender battery can double the range. The AL5 model features a Shimano 105 2x11-speed drivetrain and hydraulic disc brakes. The bike comes stock with 32mm wide tires but can be fitted with tires up to 38mm for light gravel and dirt road rides.</p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-14-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-14" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_14" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/bikes-gear/breaker_15__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><hr data-node-id="109" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="110" cl