</div></div><div></div></div></div><div class="vjs-wrapper"></div></div></div></div><p data-node-id="159" class="body-tip css-11ym6pp et3p2gv0"><a href="https://www.bicycling.com/email/bicycling-newsletter" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/email/bicycling-newsletter" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="📧  To always be in the know, sign up for our newsletter" rel="nofollow" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" class="body-btn-link css-1146q7 et3p2gv0">📧  To always be in the know, sign up for our newsletter</a></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><img width="540" height="540" alt="Headshot of Tara Seplavy" title="This is an image" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/17816e75-c3b6-4b6e-a4b0-9066a1823338_1644009404.file" size="auto" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/17816e75-c3b6-4b6e-a4b0-9066a1823338_1644009404.file" loading="lazy" class="lqip lazyloaded css-o0wq4v e1lki9i00 ls-is-cached"></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/238358/tara-seplavy/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>Tara Seplavy</span></a></span></div><div class="css-1pq7n1y e19xk9rq5">Deputy Editor</div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>As Deputy Editor, Tara Seplavy leads Bicycling’s product test team; after having previously led product development and sourcing for multiple bike brands, run World Championship winning mountain bike teams, wrenched at renowned bicycle shops in Brooklyn, raced everything from criteriums to downhill, and ridden bikes on six different continents (landing herself in hospital emergency rooms in four countries and counting). Based in Easton, Pennsylvania, Tara spends tons of time on the road and trail testing products. A familiar face at cyclocross races, crits, and bike parks in the Mid Atlantic and New England, on weekends she can often be found racing for the New York City-based CRCA/KruisCX team. When not riding a bike, or talking about them, Tara listens to a lot of ska, punk, and emo music, and consumes too much social media. &nbsp;</p></div><a href="/author/238358/tara-seplavy/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'DRAFT', 'https://example.com/thumbnail5.jpg', 'https://example.com/cover_image5.jpg', 1, '2023-03-10 13:00:00.000000', 1, '2023-03-10 13:00:00.000000', 1, false, 19, 'Add more zip to every trip with e-bikes for every type of rider.'),
        (57, 'Follow This 8-Week Century Ride Training Plan to Clock 100 Miles With Confidence', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'DRAFT', 'https://i.imgur.com/61BqlMK.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/61BqlMK.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-03-10 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (48, 'Fuel Up for Your Indoor Cycling Rides With These Tips', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">If you’re new to or interested in <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a36787763/plant-centered-diet-for-heart-health-study/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a36787763/plant-centered-diet-for-heart-health-study/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="plant-based eating" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">plant-based eating</a>, you may worry that you won’t get enough <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a33770306/protein-for-muscle-repair-after-endurance-exercise-study/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a33770306/protein-for-muscle-repair-after-endurance-exercise-study/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="protein" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">protein</a> for your active lifestyle. After all, plants usually have less protein per gram than animal foods, and they tend not to be absorbed as well. Yet, many plant-based athletes are thriving after ditching animal foods. </p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To gain some insight into the differences between animal protein vs. plant protein, we chatted with two registered dietitians: Marie Spano, M.S., R.D., a sports dietitian for the Atlanta Braves, and <a href="http://www.samanthacassetty.com/" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="http://www.samanthacassetty.com/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Samantha Cassetty," class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Samantha Cassetty,</a> M.S., R.D., a nutrition and wellness expert and co-author of <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009?ots=1&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;tag=bicycling-auto-20&amp;ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2143.a.37948187%5Bsrc%7C%5Bch%7C%5Blt%7C%5Bpid%7Ce4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noskim" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Sugar Shock" data-href="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-vars-ga-product-id="e4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04" data-affiliate="true" data-affiliate-url="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-affiliate-network="{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2bd74d91-bd6c-4123-8271-bf2ff4a3ebc1&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{},&quot;network&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;469ce69f-4798-416d-9432-eaa9954b4053&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Amazon&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{}}}" data-vars-ga-media-role="" data-vars-ga-media-type="" data-vars-ga-product-brand="amazon.com" data-vars-ga-product-price="" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="9039d339-de00-4216-9cd9-8b5dead81036" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="amazon.com" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="" data-vars-ga-gallery-id="" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" class="body-link product-links css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0" data-amazon-ascsubtag="[artid|2143.a.37948187[src|[ch|[lt|[pid|e4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04"><em>Sugar Shock</em></a>. </p><p data-node-id="2" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <em><strong><a href="https://join.bicycling.com/pubs/HR/BIC/BIC1_Plans.jsp?cds_page_id=251593&amp;cds_mag_code=BIC&amp;cds_tracking_code=edit-inline-animal-protein-vs-plant-protein" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://join.bicycling.com/pubs/HR/BIC/BIC1_Plans.jsp?cds_page_id=251593&amp;cds_mag_code=BIC&amp;cds_tracking_code=edit-inline-animal-protein-vs-plant-protein" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Get Bicycling All Access today to stay on top of the latest nutrition tips, training advice, gear reviews, and more!" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0"><mark>Get Bicycling All Access today to stay on top of the latest nutrition tips, training advice, gear reviews, and more!</mark></a></strong></em></p><h2 data-node-id="4" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">How do animal and plant proteins differ?</h2><p data-node-id="5" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein is a building block of skin, hair, teeth, nails, and major organs, and it also serves as an antibody, messenger, enzyme, transporter and storage. Protein is most known for its ability to stimulate muscle protein synthesis (MPS) for at least 24 hours in response to a single session of exercise, like cycling. In other words, it’s really important!  </p><p data-node-id="6" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein is found in both animal and plant foods. For instance, you can get protein from animal sources such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/g23099593/healthy-chicken-recipes-post-ride/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/g23099593/healthy-chicken-recipes-post-ride/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="chicken" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">chicken</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a37068537/healthiest-seafood-for-cyclists/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a37068537/healthiest-seafood-for-cyclists/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="fish" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">fish</a>, turkey, and <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a28928467/is-beef-jerky-healthy/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a28928467/is-beef-jerky-healthy/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="beef" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">beef</a>, and you can get protein from plant sources such as soy, beans, legumes, nuts, and seeds. However, not all sources are created equal. </p><p data-node-id="7" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“[Athletes] who eat only plant foods need more total protein each day because plant proteins generally aren’t as high quality as animal-based proteins,” Spano tells <em>Runner’s World</em>. <em></em></p><p data-node-id="8" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein quality often has to do with the amino acid profile of a food. As a quick refresher, <a href="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a26859247/what-is-bcaa/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a26859247/what-is-bcaa/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="amino acids" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">amino acids</a> are the building blocks of protein, which help your body build and repair muscle and regulate your <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a33459107/best-vegetables-for-immune-system/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a33459107/best-vegetables-for-immune-system/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="immune system" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">immune system</a>. There are 20 amino acids, but only nine are essential—as in, your body can’t produce them, but you need them to live. </p><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Up until recently, it was a commonly held belief that plant foods are “missing” some of the 20 essential amino acids. Yet, a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6893534/?fbclid=IwAR0jrFOYI2FG_rkPHId_pfG1pPOH7sMEDVUQSNqLX1yknOpOCjMU0BJuxf4" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6893534/?fbclid=IwAR0jrFOYI2FG_rkPHId_pfG1pPOH7sMEDVUQSNqLX1yknOpOCjMU0BJuxf4" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="recent review" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">recent review</a> of the research found that, more accurately, the amino acid distribution profile is “less optimal in plant foods than in animal foods,” meaning that some amino acids are limited in certain plant-based proteins. </p><p data-node-id="11" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">But the good news is rectifying this issue is simple. “It’s a good idea to include different plant foods, such as pulses, soy foods, whole grains, nuts, and seeds throughout the day. It will help you meet your protein needs without having to eat a giant portion of any single food,” Cassetty tells <em>Runner’s World</em>. <em></em></p><p data-node-id="12" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Another difference between animal- and plant-based proteins is the quantity of protein per volume of food. For example, 3 ounces of chicken has about 20 grams of protein, as compared to about 6 grams in 3 ounces of chickpeas and 8 grams in 3 ounces of firm tofu. </p><p data-node-id="13" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To get the same amount of protein that you would from animal foods, you need to eat more if you’re a plant-based cyclist. Cassetty recommends varying the plant-based proteins in your meal. </p><p data-node-id="14" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">She says that rather than eating 2 cups of chickpeas at 22 grams of protein, have a cup of chickpeas—at 11 grams of protein—½ cup of quinoa —at 4 grams of protein—and roasted veggies. Then drizzle 2 tablespoons of tahini—which is 5 grams of protein—on top.</p><div class="css-it8c6v ehha8ut0">This content is imported from poll. You may be able to find the same content in another format, or you may be able to find more information, at their web site.</div><div data-embed="poll" data-node-id="15" class="embed css-0 ektkw391"><iframe id="poll-25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c" title="Poll content" height="143" width="100%" aria-hidden="true" data-src="https://riddler.hearstgames.com/dist/polls.iframe.html?id=25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c&amp;type=text&amp;question=Do%20you%20need%20more%20training%20or%20nutrition%20advice%20in%20your%20riding%20life%3F&amp;answer1=Training%20for%20sure%E2%80%94I%20want%20to%20PR%20my%20next%20race%21&amp;answer2=Nutrition%E2%80%94I%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start%21&amp;siteId=3e909d2b-7135-42e6-b3e0-1b59c10468a9&amp;adCategory=undefined&amp;section=Health%20%26%20Nutrition&amp;subsection=undefined&amp;editor=undefined&amp;adsfree=false&amp;brand=bicycling&amp;authors=undefined&amp;site=bicycling&amp;stylesheet=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fsites%2Fbicycling%2Fassets%2Fcss%2Fpolls.css&amp;marketingpolls=true" class="poll lazyloaded css-vaxtlc ektkw392 " src="https://riddler.hearstgames.com/dist/polls.iframe.html?id=25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c&amp;type=text&amp;question=Do%20you%20need%20more%20training%20or%20nutrition%20advice%20in%20your%20riding%20life%3F&amp;answer1=Training%20for%20sure%E2%80%94I%20want%20to%20PR%20my%20next%20race%21&amp;answer2=Nutrition%E2%80%94I%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start%21&amp;siteId=3e909d2b-7135-42e6-b3e0-1b59c10468a9&amp;adCategory=undefined&amp;section=Health%20%26%20Nutrition&amp;subsection=undefined&amp;editor=undefined&amp;adsfree=false&amp;brand=bicycling&amp;authors=undefined&amp;site=bicycling&amp;stylesheet=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fsites%2Fbicycling%2Fassets%2Fcss%2Fpolls.css&amp;marketingpolls=true"></iframe></div><h2 data-node-id="16" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">How does your body absorb both types of protein?</h2><p data-node-id="17" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“You can get and use the building blocks—amino acids—from animal proteins easier than you can from plant proteins,” says Spano. As a matter of fact, there are two rating systems used to determine the protein bioavailability [a measure of how much a substance is able to access your body’s circulation and reach the target area] of a food: ​​the protein digestibility-corrected amino acid score (PDCAAS) and digestible indispensable amino acid score (DIAAS). </p><p data-node-id="18" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The PDCAAS system has been around since 1993 and looks at the amino acid quality of a food, whereas the newer DIAAS was proposed by the Food and Agriculture Organization of United Nations (FAO) in 2013. It determines amino acid digestibility at the end of the small intestine, providing a more accurate measure of the amounts of amino acids absorbed by the body. </p><p data-node-id="20" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Knowing the score of each individual protein is not necessary, but there are a few takeaways from these scoring systems. Mainly, soy is the only plant-based protein that scores just as high as meat and dairy. Potato, peas, and beans also come close to meat on both scales, although they are generally about <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7760812/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7760812/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="25 percent lower" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">25 percent lower</a>. </p><p data-node-id="21" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“Because those building blocks are not as bioavailable in plant proteins, you need a larger serving size of protein to meet your needs,” says Spano. In general, Spano advises aiming for a minimum of 30 to 40 grams of protein per meal if you are consuming only plant foods (as opposed to 20 to 25 grams of protein if you are consuming animal foods). </p><p data-node-id="22" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">According to the <a href="https://www.eatrightpro.org/-/media/eatrightpro-files/practice/position-and-practice-papers/position-papers/vegetarian-diet.pdf" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.eatrightpro.org/-/media/eatrightpro-files/practice/position-and-practice-papers/position-papers/vegetarian-diet.pdf" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics</a>, if you’re a vegan or vegetarian who eats a variety of plant-based proteins throughout the day, you should have no problem meeting your protein needs. And if you rely on protein supplements, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6358922/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6358922/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="research" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">research</a> suggests rice and pea protein may stimulate changes in muscle and strength just as well as whey protein. </p><h2 data-node-id="23" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">Do you need more protein on a plant-based diet?</h2><p data-node-id="24" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><a href="https://jissn.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12970-018-0242-y" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://jissn.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12970-018-0242-y" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Research" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Research</a> from the past 30 years indicates that athletes engaging in intense training may need anywhere from 1.2 to 2.0 grams of protein per kilogram (0.45 to 0.9 grams per pound) of body weight per day to maintain muscle mass. For a 150-pound rider, that’s anywhere from 68 to 135 grams of protein per day. </p><p data-node-id="25" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">A plant-based athlete may need to eat slightly more protein than an athlete who consumes animal foods, but it doesn’t have to be overly complicated, according to Cassetty. </p><p data-node-id="26" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Spano cites <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6643/11/12/3016" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6643/11/12/3016" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="one study" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">one study</a>, which found vegetarian endurance athletes need 12 percent more—or about an extra 10 grams per day—total protein compared to omnivore endurance athletes. So for that same 150-pound plant-based rider, that adds up to 78 to 145 grams of protein per day.</p><p data-node-id="27" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Again, Cassetty stresses that “it’s important to consume protein from a variety of plant sources, and to distribute that protein over all of your meals and snacks.” </p><p data-node-id="28" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Here’s what a typical day for a 150-pound plant-based eater may look like:</p><p data-node-id="29" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Muesli bowl with ½ cup uncooked oats + 3 tablespoons of hemp seeds + 1 ounce almonds + fruit = 18 grams protein</p><p data-node-id="30" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Lunch:</strong> Lentil soup with 1 ½  cups of lentil = 30 grams of protein</p><p data-node-id="31" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Snack:</strong> 1 cup of edamame = 20 grams protein</p><p data-node-id="32" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Dinner:</strong><strong></strong> 5 ounces of tempeh with rice &amp; veggies = 30 grams of protein</p><div suppresshydrationwarning="" class="css-0 e9hzx6g0"><div class="css-0 ev08twp2"><span class="css-18vfmjb ev08twp1">From: </span><a href="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a37897011/animal-protein-vs-plant-protein/" aria-label="View on Runner''s World US" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a37897011/animal-protein-vs-plant-protein/" class="css-1mkf7v ev08twp0">Runner''s World US</a></div></div><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><img width="540" height="540" alt="Headshot of Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD" title="This is an image" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/5c2a399e-9d52-452d-8bd5-f7a8da5d0a1e_1536682926.file" size="auto" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/5c2a399e-9d52-452d-8bd5-f7a8da5d0a1e_1536682926.file" loading="lazy" class="lqip lazyloaded css-o0wq4v e1lki9i00 "></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/218096/natalie-rizzo-m-s-r-d/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD</span></a></span></div><div class="css-1pq7n1y e19xk9rq5">Registered Dietitian</div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD is a New York City-based dietitian, food and nutrition writer, national speaker and owner of Nutrition a la Natalie, a sports nutrition practice. She developed a love for cooking, nutrition and fitness as an adult, which prompted a career change from advertising to nutrition. She spends most of her spare time running along the NYC waterfront and creating (and photographing) healthy and tasty recipes.</p></div><a href="/author/218096/natalie-rizzo-m-s-r-d/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/fSjsOA3.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/fSjsOA3.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:25:13.156751', 1, '2023-03-10 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 1, 'Plus, do you need to eat more of this macronutrient if you’re plant-based? '),
        (50, 'The Best Ice Bath Temperature and Duration to Reap Recovery Benefits', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">If you’re new to or interested in <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a36787763/plant-centered-diet-for-heart-health-study/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a36787763/plant-centered-diet-for-heart-health-study/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="plant-based eating" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">plant-based eating</a>, you may worry that you won’t get enough <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a33770306/protein-for-muscle-repair-after-endurance-exercise-study/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/news/a33770306/protein-for-muscle-repair-after-endurance-exercise-study/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="protein" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">protein</a> for your active lifestyle. After all, plants usually have less protein per gram than animal foods, and they tend not to be absorbed as well. Yet, many plant-based athletes are thriving after ditching animal foods. </p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To gain some insight into the differences between animal protein vs. plant protein, we chatted with two registered dietitians: Marie Spano, M.S., R.D., a sports dietitian for the Atlanta Braves, and <a href="http://www.samanthacassetty.com/" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="http://www.samanthacassetty.com/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Samantha Cassetty," class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Samantha Cassetty,</a> M.S., R.D., a nutrition and wellness expert and co-author of <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009?ots=1&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;tag=bicycling-auto-20&amp;ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2143.a.37948187%5Bsrc%7C%5Bch%7C%5Blt%7C%5Bpid%7Ce4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noskim" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Sugar Shock" data-href="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-vars-ga-product-id="e4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04" data-affiliate="true" data-affiliate-url="https://www.amazon.com/Sugar-Shock-Hidden-Smart-Swaps/dp/1950785009" data-affiliate-network="{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2bd74d91-bd6c-4123-8271-bf2ff4a3ebc1&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{},&quot;network&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;469ce69f-4798-416d-9432-eaa9954b4053&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Amazon&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{}}}" data-vars-ga-media-role="" data-vars-ga-media-type="" data-vars-ga-product-brand="amazon.com" data-vars-ga-product-price="" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="9039d339-de00-4216-9cd9-8b5dead81036" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="amazon.com" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="" data-vars-ga-gallery-id="" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" class="body-link product-links css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0" data-amazon-ascsubtag="[artid|2143.a.37948187[src|[ch|[lt|[pid|e4a2fcd8-4a1a-4f63-a1eb-6441e63feb04"><em>Sugar Shock</em></a>. </p><p data-node-id="2" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <em><strong><a href="https://join.bicycling.com/pubs/HR/BIC/BIC1_Plans.jsp?cds_page_id=251593&amp;cds_mag_code=BIC&amp;cds_tracking_code=edit-inline-animal-protein-vs-plant-protein" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://join.bicycling.com/pubs/HR/BIC/BIC1_Plans.jsp?cds_page_id=251593&amp;cds_mag_code=BIC&amp;cds_tracking_code=edit-inline-animal-protein-vs-plant-protein" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Get Bicycling All Access today to stay on top of the latest nutrition tips, training advice, gear reviews, and more!" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0"><mark>Get Bicycling All Access today to stay on top of the latest nutrition tips, training advice, gear reviews, and more!</mark></a></strong></em></p><h2 data-node-id="4" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">How do animal and plant proteins differ?</h2><p data-node-id="5" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein is a building block of skin, hair, teeth, nails, and major organs, and it also serves as an antibody, messenger, enzyme, transporter and storage. Protein is most known for its ability to stimulate muscle protein synthesis (MPS) for at least 24 hours in response to a single session of exercise, like cycling. In other words, it’s really important!  </p><p data-node-id="6" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein is found in both animal and plant foods. For instance, you can get protein from animal sources such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/g23099593/healthy-chicken-recipes-post-ride/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/g23099593/healthy-chicken-recipes-post-ride/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="chicken" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">chicken</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a37068537/healthiest-seafood-for-cyclists/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a37068537/healthiest-seafood-for-cyclists/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="fish" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">fish</a>, turkey, and <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a28928467/is-beef-jerky-healthy/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a28928467/is-beef-jerky-healthy/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="beef" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">beef</a>, and you can get protein from plant sources such as soy, beans, legumes, nuts, and seeds. However, not all sources are created equal. </p><p data-node-id="7" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“[Athletes] who eat only plant foods need more total protein each day because plant proteins generally aren’t as high quality as animal-based proteins,” Spano tells <em>Runner’s World</em>. <em></em></p><p data-node-id="8" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Protein quality often has to do with the amino acid profile of a food. As a quick refresher, <a href="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a26859247/what-is-bcaa/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a26859247/what-is-bcaa/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="amino acids" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">amino acids</a> are the building blocks of protein, which help your body build and repair muscle and regulate your <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a33459107/best-vegetables-for-immune-system/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/health-nutrition/a33459107/best-vegetables-for-immune-system/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="immune system" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">immune system</a>. There are 20 amino acids, but only nine are essential—as in, your body can’t produce them, but you need them to live. </p><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Up until recently, it was a commonly held belief that plant foods are “missing” some of the 20 essential amino acids. Yet, a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6893534/?fbclid=IwAR0jrFOYI2FG_rkPHId_pfG1pPOH7sMEDVUQSNqLX1yknOpOCjMU0BJuxf4" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6893534/?fbclid=IwAR0jrFOYI2FG_rkPHId_pfG1pPOH7sMEDVUQSNqLX1yknOpOCjMU0BJuxf4" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="recent review" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">recent review</a> of the research found that, more accurately, the amino acid distribution profile is “less optimal in plant foods than in animal foods,” meaning that some amino acids are limited in certain plant-based proteins. </p><p data-node-id="11" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">But the good news is rectifying this issue is simple. “It’s a good idea to include different plant foods, such as pulses, soy foods, whole grains, nuts, and seeds throughout the day. It will help you meet your protein needs without having to eat a giant portion of any single food,” Cassetty tells <em>Runner’s World</em>. <em></em></p><p data-node-id="12" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Another difference between animal- and plant-based proteins is the quantity of protein per volume of food. For example, 3 ounces of chicken has about 20 grams of protein, as compared to about 6 grams in 3 ounces of chickpeas and 8 grams in 3 ounces of firm tofu. </p><p data-node-id="13" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To get the same amount of protein that you would from animal foods, you need to eat more if you’re a plant-based cyclist. Cassetty recommends varying the plant-based proteins in your meal. </p><p data-node-id="14" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">She says that rather than eating 2 cups of chickpeas at 22 grams of protein, have a cup of chickpeas—at 11 grams of protein—½ cup of quinoa —at 4 grams of protein—and roasted veggies. Then drizzle 2 tablespoons of tahini—which is 5 grams of protein—on top.</p><div class="css-it8c6v ehha8ut0">This content is imported from poll. You may be able to find the same content in another format, or you may be able to find more information, at their web site.</div><div data-embed="poll" data-node-id="15" class="embed css-0 ektkw391"><iframe id="poll-25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c" title="Poll content" height="143" width="100%" aria-hidden="true" data-src="https://riddler.hearstgames.com/dist/polls.iframe.html?id=25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c&amp;type=text&amp;question=Do%20you%20need%20more%20training%20or%20nutrition%20advice%20in%20your%20riding%20life%3F&amp;answer1=Training%20for%20sure%E2%80%94I%20want%20to%20PR%20my%20next%20race%21&amp;answer2=Nutrition%E2%80%94I%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start%21&amp;siteId=3e909d2b-7135-42e6-b3e0-1b59c10468a9&amp;adCategory=undefined&amp;section=Health%20%26%20Nutrition&amp;subsection=undefined&amp;editor=undefined&amp;adsfree=false&amp;brand=bicycling&amp;authors=undefined&amp;site=bicycling&amp;stylesheet=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fsites%2Fbicycling%2Fassets%2Fcss%2Fpolls.css&amp;marketingpolls=true" class="poll lazyloaded css-vaxtlc ektkw392 " src="https://riddler.hearstgames.com/dist/polls.iframe.html?id=25170335-0c22-42ce-9f6b-121a80f0676b_f75885db6674c&amp;type=text&amp;question=Do%20you%20need%20more%20training%20or%20nutrition%20advice%20in%20your%20riding%20life%3F&amp;answer1=Training%20for%20sure%E2%80%94I%20want%20to%20PR%20my%20next%20race%21&amp;answer2=Nutrition%E2%80%94I%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start%21&amp;siteId=3e909d2b-7135-42e6-b3e0-1b59c10468a9&amp;adCategory=undefined&amp;section=Health%20%26%20Nutrition&amp;subsection=undefined&amp;editor=undefined&amp;adsfree=false&amp;brand=bicycling&amp;authors=undefined&amp;site=bicycling&amp;stylesheet=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bicycling.com%2Fsites%2Fbicycling%2Fassets%2Fcss%2Fpolls.css&amp;marketingpolls=true"></iframe></div><h2 data-node-id="16" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">How does your body absorb both types of protein?</h2><p data-node-id="17" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“You can get and use the building blocks—amino acids—from animal proteins easier than you can from plant proteins,” says Spano. As a matter of fact, there are two rating systems used to determine the protein bioavailability [a measure of how much a substance is able to access your body’s circulation and reach the target area] of a food: ​​the protein digestibility-corrected amino acid score (PDCAAS) and digestible indispensable amino acid score (DIAAS). </p><p data-node-id="18" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The PDCAAS system has been around since 1993 and looks at the amino acid quality of a food, whereas the newer DIAAS was proposed by the Food and Agriculture Organization of United Nations (FAO) in 2013. It determines amino acid digestibility at the end of the small intestine, providing a more accurate measure of the amounts of amino acids absorbed by the body. </p><p data-node-id="20" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Knowing the score of each individual protein is not necessary, but there are a few takeaways from these scoring systems. Mainly, soy is the only plant-based protein that scores just as high as meat and dairy. Potato, peas, and beans also come close to meat on both scales, although they are generally about <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7760812/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7760812/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="25 percent lower" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">25 percent lower</a>. </p><p data-node-id="21" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">“Because those building blocks are not as bioavailable in plant proteins, you need a larger serving size of protein to meet your needs,” says Spano. In general, Spano advises aiming for a minimum of 30 to 40 grams of protein per meal if you are consuming only plant foods (as opposed to 20 to 25 grams of protein if you are consuming animal foods). </p><p data-node-id="22" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">According to the <a href="https://www.eatrightpro.org/-/media/eatrightpro-files/practice/position-and-practice-papers/position-papers/vegetarian-diet.pdf" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.eatrightpro.org/-/media/eatrightpro-files/practice/position-and-practice-papers/position-papers/vegetarian-diet.pdf" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics</a>, if you’re a vegan or vegetarian who eats a variety of plant-based proteins throughout the day, you should have no problem meeting your protein needs. And if you rely on protein supplements, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6358922/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6358922/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="research" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">research</a> suggests rice and pea protein may stimulate changes in muscle and strength just as well as whey protein. </p><h2 data-node-id="23" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">Do you need more protein on a plant-based diet?</h2><p data-node-id="24" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><a href="https://jissn.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12970-018-0242-y" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://jissn.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12970-018-0242-y" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Research" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Research</a> from the past 30 years indicates that athletes engaging in intense training may need anywhere from 1.2 to 2.0 grams of protein per kilogram (0.45 to 0.9 grams per pound) of body weight per day to maintain muscle mass. For a 150-pound rider, that’s anywhere from 68 to 135 grams of protein per day. </p><p data-node-id="25" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">A plant-based athlete may need to eat slightly more protein than an athlete who consumes animal foods, but it doesn’t have to be overly complicated, according to Cassetty. </p><p data-node-id="26" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Spano cites <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6643/11/12/3016" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.mdpi.com/2072-6643/11/12/3016" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="one study" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">one study</a>, which found vegetarian endurance athletes need 12 percent more—or about an extra 10 grams per day—total protein compared to omnivore endurance athletes. So for that same 150-pound plant-based rider, that adds up to 78 to 145 grams of protein per day.</p><p data-node-id="27" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Again, Cassetty stresses that “it’s important to consume protein from a variety of plant sources, and to distribute that protein over all of your meals and snacks.” </p><p data-node-id="28" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Here’s what a typical day for a 150-pound plant-based eater may look like:</p><p data-node-id="29" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Muesli bowl with ½ cup uncooked oats + 3 tablespoons of hemp seeds + 1 ounce almonds + fruit = 18 grams protein</p><p data-node-id="30" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Lunch:</strong> Lentil soup with 1 ½  cups of lentil = 30 grams of protein</p><p data-node-id="31" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Snack:</strong> 1 cup of edamame = 20 grams protein</p><p data-node-id="32" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">→ <strong>Dinner:</strong><strong></strong> 5 ounces of tempeh with rice &amp; veggies = 30 grams of protein</p><div suppresshydrationwarning="" class="css-0 e9hzx6g0"><div class="css-0 ev08twp2"><span class="css-18vfmjb ev08twp1">From: </span><a href="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a37897011/animal-protein-vs-plant-protein/" aria-label="View on Runner''s World US" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.runnersworld.com/nutrition-weight-loss/a37897011/animal-protein-vs-plant-protein/" class="css-1mkf7v ev08twp0">Runner''s World US</a></div></div><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><img width="540" height="540" alt="Headshot of Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD" title="This is an image" fetchpriority="auto" decoding="async" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/5c2a399e-9d52-452d-8bd5-f7a8da5d0a1e_1536682926.file" size="auto" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/rover/profile_photos/5c2a399e-9d52-452d-8bd5-f7a8da5d0a1e_1536682926.file" loading="lazy" class="lqip lazyloaded css-o0wq4v e1lki9i00 "></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/218096/natalie-rizzo-m-s-r-d/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD</span></a></span></div><div class="css-1pq7n1y e19xk9rq5">Registered Dietitian</div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Natalie Rizzo, MS, RD is a New York City-based dietitian, food and nutrition writer, national speaker and owner of Nutrition a la Natalie, a sports nutrition practice. She developed a love for cooking, nutrition and fitness as an adult, which prompted a career change from advertising to nutrition. She spends most of her spare time running along the NYC waterfront and creating (and photographing) healthy and tasty recipes.</p></div><a href="/author/218096/natalie-rizzo-m-s-r-d/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/pvC6vtr.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/pvC6vtr.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:25:13.156751', 1, '2023-03-10 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 1, 'Plus, do you need to eat more of this macronutrient if you’re plant-based? '),
        (52, 'These Cycling Tips for Beginners Will Make Riding More Fun', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/I9j2dEI.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/I9j2dEI.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-03-05 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (53, 'Beginner Road Biking Tips to Help You Ride With Confidence', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/7mM9WZU.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/7mM9WZU.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-01-10 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (54, 'The 10 Best Indoor Bike Trainers', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/dVSXECb.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/dVSXECb.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-03-10 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (55, 'The Ultimate Guide to High-Intensity Interval Training for Cyclists', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/GtnBLfS.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/GtnBLfS.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-03-11 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (56, 'A 4-Week Training Plan to Help You Build Your Endurance Base Fast', '<div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To the uninitiated, entering our first cyclocross race can seem a little scary. Why do the racers dismount and run with their bikes? What''s with all the hills - and jumping over barriers? Are the fans always this rowdy?<br></p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">We have you covered with some answers, and the three essential skills you need to know in order to try a race. Practice, get confident, and you''ll be forking over your first cyclocross race entry fee in no time.</p><h2 data-node-id="2" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">No need to be intimidated</h2><p data-node-id="3" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">The spirit of cyclocross is fun, welcoming and a bit of a party, complete with “guests” -rowdy, possibly­ ­inebriated but well-­intentioned spectators cheering from the sidelines. “There’s something for everyone in ’cross,” says six-time ­national champion­ and longtime ambassador of the sport, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.instagram.com/timjohnsoncx/?hl=en" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Tim Johnson" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Tim Johnson</a>. “Where road racing might seem intimidating with its tactics and road rash, ’cross is simple and anything goes.”  And because events take place in the fall and winter, you get a workout that carries you through the off-season, too. </p><div data-node-id="4" data-interactive="WatchNext-1" class="journey-unblur-content css-0 e10xr3vp6"></div><h2 data-node-id="5" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How a cyclocross race works</h2><p data-node-id="6" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Riders complete multiple laps on timed, closed, off-road courses that include obstacles such as <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047943/cyclocross-skills-overcome-any-barrier/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="wooden barriers" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">wooden barriers</a>, <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/racing/a20047539/come-out-on-top-the-cyclocross-run-up/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="steep run-ups" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">steep run-ups</a>, and sand pits that <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/training/a20047308/get-faster-at-cross-no-intervals-required/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="require riders to dismount and carry their bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">require riders to dismount and carry their bikes</a>. Most amateur events take 40 to 45 minutes to finish. Riders wear mountain bike shoes with grippy treads but ride ­<a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="cyclocross-specific bikes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">cyclocross-specific bikes</a>, though some races allow mountain bikes. Check with the organizer before you enter. </p><h2 data-node-id="8" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">Three essentials skills to know</h2><p data-node-id="9" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Getting on and off your bike in a smooth and fast motion is one of the most important skills to learn in cyclocross. Carrying your bike while you''re running is high on the list, too.  In ''cross terms, these skills are referred to as the “dismount,” the “remount,” and “shouldering.” <br></p><p data-node-id="10" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">While these skills are considered cyclocross basics, there''s nothing basic about them. Good technique - the kind that comes from putting the time and practice in - makes a huge difference at the finish line. <br></p><h2 data-node-id="11" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to dismount your bike</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="12" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross superprestige boom" title="CYCLOCROSS SUPERPRESTIGE BOOM" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/british-thomas-pidcock-pictured-in-action-during-the-mens-news-photo-1670354772.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">DAVID STOCKMAN</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="13" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"> As you approach an obstacle, slow down and coast. With hands on the hoods, unclip your right foot, then swing your right leg back and around the saddle, bringing it between the bike and your left leg. As the bike slows, step to the ground with your right foot and unclip your left foot. Give yourself time to take a few strides before the obstacle.<br></p><h2 data-node-id="14" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to remount your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="15" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="cyclocross bel berencross" title="CYCLOCROSS-BEL-BERENCROSS" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="683" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/belgiums-victor-van-de-putte-competes-in-the-mens-elite-news-photo-1670354390.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">JASPER JACOBS</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="16" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"></p><p data-node-id="17" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Keep moving forward and, with your bike on the ground and hands on the bar, point the bike in the direction you need to go. Step forward with your left foot and swing your right leg behind you and over the saddle. Try to land (gently) on the inside of your right thigh, then slide onto the saddle. Start a pedaling motion, find the pedals, and clip in.</p><h2 data-node-id="19" class="body-h3 css-jtjq1o et3p2gv0">How to shoulder your bike </h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="20" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="1st dendermonde world cup 2020  men elite" title="1st Dendermonde World Cup 2020 - Men Elite" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="682" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/wout-van-aert-of-belgium-and-team-jumbo-visma-mathieu-van-news-photo-1670353583.jpg?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">Luc Claessen</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><p data-node-id="21" class="body-text css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">To shoulder your bike, wrap your right arm around and under the down tube, hold it with your right hand, and rest the top tube on your shoulder. Grab the left side of the handlebar in your other hand to keep your wheel steady<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"><div class="css-1me4wps e19xk9rq7"><span class="css-irehmq e19xk9rq1"><svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="css-syyu3a e19xk9rq0"><title>Bicycling</title><desc>Bicycling Lettermark logo</desc><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M66.138 36.165c-2.319 8.123-3.93 10.432-9.672 10.432h-3.434c-1.307 0-1.715-.098-1.307-1.71l5.537-19.26c.408-1.505 1.01-1.703 2.327-1.703v-.003h1.205c7.56 0 7.96 3.014 5.344 12.244Zm-6.453 30.098c-2.218 7.933-3.83 10.531-10.378 10.531h-4.945c-1.305 0-1.808-.099-1.305-1.695l6.046-20.98c.407-1.505.806-1.605 2.318-1.605h2.816c7.768 0 8.469 3.109 5.448 13.75ZM72.184 49.01c11.18-1.505 15.016-5.212 16.934-11.641 3.424-11.739-1.319-19.365-26.91-19.365V18H28.645l-1.513 5.319c6.458 0 7.355 1.607 5.647 7.431l-11.49 39.734c-1.614 5.627-3.432 6.923-9.775 6.923L10 82.727h39.809c23.284 0 30.036-4.02 33.063-14.152 3.02-10.13-.605-15.96-11.186-18.06-1.32-.298-1.114-1.3.498-1.506Z" fill="#000"></path></svg></span><div><div class="css-3sqxrq e19xk9rq6"><span class="css-0 e19xk9rq4"><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-njmgv8 epl65fo4"><span>whit yost</span></a></span></div><div class="css-11ash57 e19xk9rq3"><p>Since getting hooked on pro cycling while watching Lance Armstrong win the 1993 U.S. Pro Championship in Philadelphia, longtime Bicycling contributor Whit Yost has raced on Belgian cobbles, helped build a European pro team, and piloted that team from Malaysia to Mont Ventoux as an assistant director sportif. These days, he lives with his wife and son in Pennsylvania, spending his days serving as an assistant middle school principal and his nights playing Dungeons &amp; Dragons.</p></div><a href="/author/209786/whit-yost/" class="epl65fo3 css-2m8fjc epl65fo4">Read full bio</a></div></div></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/9gsK2M4.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/9gsK2M4.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:36:47.281414', 1, '2023-03-12 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 20, 'Once you get these skills down, you''re ready to try your first ''cross race '),
        (58, 'Common Bicycling Repairs You Can Master at Home', '<div class="standard-container content-container article-container css-1nvx29v ewisyje3"><div class="content-lead css-trzem2 ewisyje6"><div class="__resp-container css-1ui7hop e15x3v910"><div data-embed="embed-video" class="video-player css-1jlky5r e1ou1fny0"><div data-embed-id="0cf04f78-588e-4abb-a392-905e2315ee76" data-aspect-ratio="16:9" data-position="3" data-dock="true" data-disable-ads="false" data-sticky="true" data-muted="true" data-autoplay="true" class="glimmerPlayer video-loader media-loader css-1xcc6xp e1k9i8iw0 playerLoaded fullyLoaded glimmer-sticky-wrapper glimmer-unsticky" style="height: auto;"><div playsinline="true" class="video-js vjs-default-skin vjs-big-play-centered vjs-paused vjs-workinghover vjs-v7 vjs-user-active vjs-fluid hearstPlayer-0cf04f78-588e-4abb-a392-905e2315ee76-1-dimensions vjs-controls-enabled vjs-dock vjs-videojs-share vjs-hls-quality-selector glimmer-sticky-player" id="hearstPlayer-0cf04f78-588e-4abb-a392-905e2315ee76-1" tabindex="-1" lang="en" translate="no" role="region" aria-label="Video Player" aria-labelledby="hearstPlayer-0cf04f78-588e-4abb-a392-905e2315ee76-1 vjs-dock-title-1" aria-describedby="vjs-dock-description-2"><video id="hearstPlayer-0cf04f78-588e-4abb-a392-905e2315ee76-1_html5_api" class="vjs-tech" playsinline="playsinline" tabindex="-1" muted="muted" preload="false" poster="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/team-ineos-pinarello-bike-mechanic-wash-detail-view-during-news-photo-1645561596.jpg?crop=1xw:0.84334xh;center,top&amp;resize=1120:*" aria-labelledby="vjs-dock-title-1" aria-describedby="vjs-dock-description-2" src="blob:https://www.bicycling.com/ca4347c9-6691-4409-92ce-f476b0c65114"></video><div class="vjs-poster" tabindex="-1" aria-disabled="false" style="background-image: url(&quot;https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/team-ineos-pinarello-bike-mechanic-wash-detail-view-during-news-photo-1645561596.jpg?crop=1xw:0.84334xh;cent