a-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000IZEGYS" data-vars-ga-product-brand="Pedro''s" data-vars-ga-product-id="9eaf6776-05c5-4876-9b60-0ee2951ecc84" data-vars-ga-product-price="$22.75" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="eb78c3d8-e36e-4275-8d6e-b968a1e42160" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="Pedro''s" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="Cleaners" data-vars-ga-gallery-id="e143da2f-a302-49be-98df-bbdb4d093105" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" data-vars-ga-sku="B000IZEGYS" data-vars-ga-magento-tracking="1" role="button" data-ab-label="ProdClick" class="product-btn-link en6kra60 css-11cr832 epl65fo4" data-amazon-ascsubtag="[artid|2143.a.35386346[src|[ch|[lt|[pid|9eaf6776-05c5-4876-9b60-0ee2951ecc84">$23 at Amazon</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><hr data-node-id="25" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="26" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">THE WASH</h2><div size="medium" data-embed="body-image" data-node-id="27" class="align-center size-medium embed css-1736von e1xqj1sx4"><div class="css-uwraif e1xqj1sx3"><img alt="how to clean a bike" title="how to clean a bike" loading="lazy" width="4480" height="2984" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent; width: 100%; height: auto;" sizes="100vw" srcset="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=640:* 640w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=768:* 980w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=980:* 1120w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=980:* 1200w, https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=980:* 1920w" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/staff-memebr-of-polands-ccc-team-cycling-team-washes-bike-news-photo-1612274966.?resize=980:*" class="css-0 exi4f7p0"><div class="css-swqnqv e1xqj1sx2"><figcaption class="css-1am3yn9 enfs9c50"><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd2">ANNE-CHRISTINE POUJOULAT</span><span class="css-1kkg07a e6iqukd0">//</span><span class="css-zwwov0 e6iqukd1">Getty Images</span></figcaption></div></div></div><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" class="breaker-ad"><div class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-1lttmkl e152u5os0"><div class="css-1cy8om4 e1v257yr0">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2" class="ad-container css-14b96eg e1hka4w80"><div id="gpt_lb_2" class="gpt-adslot noskim" style="display: none;"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/36117602/hdm-bicycling/repair/breaker_4__container__" style="border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center; width: 728px; height: 0px;"></div></div></div></div></section><p data-node-id="28" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Step 1: Chain<br></strong>Use a degreaser and turn the cranks backward so that it gets on every link. After about five to 10 minutes, rinse with a gentle stream of water from the hose. If the chain is still grimy, apply small drops of dish soap as you would with lube. Grip the chain in the rough side of your sponge, then turn the cranks for several rotations. Rinse.</p><p data-node-id="29" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Step 2: <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/repair/a20014110/5-ways-youre-wrecking-your-drivetrain/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/repair/a20014110/5-ways-youre-wrecking-your-drivetrain/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Drivetrain" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Drivetrain<br></a></strong>Dip a stiff-bristled brush into one of your pre-filled buckets and scrub the chainrings. We recommend using a bottle brush or toothbrush to get into crevices around the teeth, pulleys, and rings. Then rinse with a gentle stream of water, and repeat if you still see any lingering crud. Next, grab your rear wheel and drip dish soap onto the cassette, scrub, then rinse. Repeat if necessary.</p><p data-node-id="30" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Step 3: Frame<br></strong>Dip a clean, soft sponge into your second (fresh) bucket. Soap up the frame, working your way from front to back, then rinse. If you have caliper brakes, clean the pads with the abrasive side of the sponge.</p><p data-node-id="31" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0"><strong>Step 4: Wheels<br></strong>We recommend using softer, bigger brushes for tires and rims so you can get into every nook and cranny with minimal effort. Dunk your brush into the bucket you used for your frame. Starting at the valve, scrub all the way around the wheel. Hit the spokes and hub, then flip the wheel to get to the opposite side. Repeat on the other wheel, then rinse. (If you have <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20023166/the-beginners-guide-to-disc-brakes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20023166/the-beginners-guide-to-disc-brakes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="disc brakes" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">disc brakes</a>, use the soft side of a clean sponge with soap and water on the rotors.)</p><hr data-node-id="32" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="33" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">THE FINISH</h2><p data-node-id="34" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">Reattach the wheels and spin the cranks to make sure the drivetrain runs smoothly. Wipe everything down with a dry, clean cloth, or let it air dry in the sun. <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/repair/a23087205/how-to-use-bike-chain-lube/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/repair/a23087205/how-to-use-bike-chain-lube/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Lube your chain" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">Lube your chain</a>.<br></p><div class="css-2ok9l4 e13rjwo40"></div><div id="journey-inline" class="css-ciejky e1cslvxz0"></div></div></div>', 'PUBLISH', 'https://i.imgur.com/3Op7SrJ.png', 'https://i.imgur.com/3Op7SrJ.png', 1, '2023-03-16 03:48:54.538484', 1, '2023-03-11 13:45:00.000000', 1, false, 21, 'The slightly obsessive (but totally doable) guide to making your bike shine.'),
