</div></div><div class="vjs-wrapper vjs-unsticky"></div></div></div></div><div class="article-body-content article-body standard-body-content css-z6i669 ewisyje7"><p data-node-id="0" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">If we learned one thing about riding in 2021, it’s that more and more people were getting on their bikes for exercise and some adventure. And you probably realized the more you go on a particularly muddy <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/rides/g23509318/trails-near-me/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/rides/g23509318/trails-near-me/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="ride on the trails" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">ride on the trails</a>—or want to bring your <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20050631/how-to-choose-an-indoor-bike-trainer/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a20050631/how-to-choose-an-indoor-bike-trainer/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="bike indoors" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">bike indoors</a> for a training session—that you’ll need to give it a good scrub. </p><p data-node-id="1" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">But even if your bike isn’t completely caked in mud and dirt, it still needs some TLC every so often. We recommend cleaning your <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a22577467/best-road-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a22577467/best-road-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="road bike" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">road bike</a> monthly (or every 20 to 25 rides) and a <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/mountain-bike/a20048810/best-mountain-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/mountain-bike/a20048810/best-mountain-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="mountain" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">mountain</a> or <a href="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.bicycling.com/bikes-gear/a24229215/best-cyclocross-bikes/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="’cross" class="body-link css-qlm9kn et3p2gv0">’cross</a> bike more often.</p><p data-node-id="2" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">If you need some guidance, watch the video above for a demo on how to properly clean a bike, and keep reading for a few tips and tricks to make the cleaning process less of a hassle.</p><hr data-node-id="5" class="css-18pb4rg et3p2gv0"><h2 data-node-id="6" class="body-h2 css-f5aiel et3p2gv0">WHAT YOU NEED</h2><p data-node-id="7" class="css-18vfmjb et3p2gv0">You’ll need these everyday household items to clean your bike:<br><br>1. Clean shop rags or old cotton T-shirts (<em>free!</em>)<br>2. <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B086D7SX8K?ots=1&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;tag=bicycling-auto-20&amp;ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2143.a.35386346%5Bsrc%7C%5Bch%7C%5Blt%7C%5Bpid%7C0435908c-7c94-4b1a-a202-f0fdabd5bae2" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noskim" data-vars-ga-product-brand="Holikme" data-vars-ga-product-id="0435908c-7c94-4b1a-a202-f0fdabd5bae2" data-vars-ga-product-price="$9.95" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="Holikme" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-id="" data-affiliate="true" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B086D7SX8K" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Bottle brushes" data-href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B086D7SX8K" data-affiliate-url="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B086D7SX8K" data-affiliate-network="{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;2bd74d91-bd6c-4123-8271-bf2ff4a3ebc1&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{},&quot;network&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;469ce69f-4798-416d-9432-eaa9954b4053&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Amazon&quot;,&quot;metadata&quot;:{}}}" data-vars-ga-media-role="" dat